    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="874"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d874">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12842.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to Mexico.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 13, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>206. From the details which you give we feel sure that you have made the best
                    arrangements possible under the circumstances and we congratulate you most
                    cordially. The people of the United States <pb facs="0702" n="586"
                        xml:id="pg_586"/> and the foreigners in Mexico will feel greatly relieved
                    when the agreement is carried out and the peaceful transfer of the government is
                    made. Please present our compliments when you have opportunity to both General
                    Carranza and the Governor of the District and say that we trust that this will
                    be the beginning of an era of peace, prosperity and progress for Mexico.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
